Newly listed BUA Foods Plc led the rally at the Nigerian Exchange (NGX) yesterday as Nigerian equities netted N23 billion in capital gains. Benchmark indices at the stock market indicated average gain of 0.1 per cent, equivalent to net capital gains of N23 billion. With this, the average return so far this year rose to 2.8 per cent. The All Share Index (ASI)- the value-based index that tracks all share prices at the NGX, rose from its opening index of 43,854.42 points to close at 43,897.13 points. Aggregate market value of all quoted equities rose from its opening value of N23.651 trillion to close at N23.628 trillion.   UBA’s Leo marks 4th anniversary     N10/litre excise duty’ll hurt output, revenues, says MAN     Govt’s 0.25% profit tax to fund NASENI   The positive overall market performance was driven by gains by BUA Foods and 27 other stocks. BUA Foods led the rally with a gain of N5.30 or 9.96 per cent to close at N58.50 per share. This pushed the newly listed company’s market capitalization above the trillion naira threshold to N1.05 trillion.   BUA Foods was listed by way of introduction last week. A total of 18 billion ordinary shares of 50 kobo each were listed at N40 per share. This represents a capital gain of 46.25 per cent in three days. With a market capitalization of N1 trillion, BUA Foods has joined the league of the most capitalized quoted companies which includes another member of the BUA Group, BUA Cement; Nestle Nigeria, Airtel Africa, MTN Nigeria Communications and the most capitalized quoted company, Dangote Cement Plc. - Advertisement - Other top gainers included MRS, which rose by 9.72 per cent to close at N13.55. PZ Cussons Nigeria, which rose by 8.53 per cent to close at N7. Total turnover stood at 310.9 million shares valued at N8.6 billion. BUA Foods was the most active stock with a turnover of 101.4 million shares worth N5.9 billion.